commentary: Osinde to Mohammad Hafeez, OUT Given out and Hafeez goes for UDRS. LBW. commentary: Baidwan to Misbah-ul-Haq, 1 run almost caught A better fielder would have got to it? Maybe .. may be not. Well, a taller one would certainly have. It was the surprise bouncer from Baidwan and it was outside off stump. Misbah mistimed the pull and it popped just over square-leg. Jimmy Hansra was stationed there forward of square-leg and he leaped but the ball just about eluded him. It went very slowly but it just about sailed over. Ooh!

commentary: Saeed Ajmal to Surkari, OUT loud shout for lbw The quick seam-up delivery. They go for another review as the umpire negates this one as well! It landed full in length on the leg stump line, moved across with the arm, hit the pad in front of the middle - the ball clipped the pad before it hit the bat - and it would have hit the off stump. Looks out. And the verdict is OUT. Harper has to reverse another decision. And Surkari trudges off in complete disappointment

Looks out. And the verdict is OUT. Harper has to reverse another decision. And Surkari trudges off in complete disappointment

commentary: Shahid Afridi to Hansra, OUT Shahid Afridi has done it again. It was that typical drifting and skidding slider. It landed on a good length around off and hurried on towards the off stump. Hansra makes a mistake of trying to cut. He tries to bring the bat down in an hurry but the ball is quicker. The off stump is pegged back/. A very fine innings but it's over now.
shortText: Shahid Afridi to Hansra, OUT
text: Shahid Afridi has done it again. It was that typical drifting and skidding slider. It landed on a good length around off and hurried on towards the off stump. Hansra makes a mistake of trying to cut. He tries to bring the bat down in an hurry but the ball is quicker. The off stump is pegged back/. A very fine innings but it's over now.

commentary: Shahid Afridi to Baidwan, OUT What a quick ripper! It was the pacy seam-up delivery. Afridi the leggie had transformed into Afridi the pacer. It landed full in length and breached the defenses of a surprised Baidwan. He had no clue and hence, no chance to save his stumps. The ball rushed through the hurried poke, hit the pad and fell on the stumps. Pakistan fans would remember the dismissal of Greg Blewett (or was it Steve Waugh)

Pakistan fans would remember the dismissal of Greg Blewett (or was it Steve Waugh)

commentary: Shahid Afridi to Gordon, OUT Afridi throws his head back and roars as he looks up to the sky. Wahab has taken a good catch in the end, after misjudging initially. It was the googly and Gordon skied the slog. Wahab came in from the deep, almost looked as if he would not take it as he stuttered as he came near the ball and then lunged out to take a good catch in the end.
